      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Consider a financial services team processing thousands of invoices daily. Manual data entry is error-prone and slow, but integrating Nanonets OCR S can automate extraction of fields like vendor names, dates, and amounts. By feeding scanned invoices into the API, the system populates accounting software directly, reducing processing time from minutes to seconds per document. This use case highlights the model's ability to handle varied invoice templates without custom training, thanks to its pre-trained robustness."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementation involves setting up a pipeline where invoices are uploaded to cloud storage, triggered via webhooks to call the OCR API, and results are parsed into structured data. For example, extracted text can be matched against regex patterns to identify key fields, with confidence scores flagging low-quality extractions for human review. In production, this has shown to cut operational costs by up to 70%, based on internal benchmarks with over 10,000 documents."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To extend this, combine Nanonets OCR S with a validation service to cross-check extracted data against purchase orders. This reduces errors in downstream systems like ERP platforms. The model's low latency—typically under 200ms per invoice—ensures real-time feedback in user-facing applications, such as mobile apps for receipt scanning."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance Benchmarks and Latency"
