        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nanonets OCR S is optimized for speed, with inference times averaging 150ms on a T4 GPU for a standard A4 document at 300 DPI. In benchmark tests against the ICDAR 2019 dataset, it achieves 96.2% word-level accuracy, outperforming many open-source alternatives in mixed-script environments. The F16 precision reduces memory usage to approximately 1.5GB per instance, allowing higher concurrency on cost-effective hardware."
          }
