      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comparing Nanonets OCR S with Alternatives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When evaluating OCR solutions, factors like accuracy, latency, and integration ease are critical. Nanonets OCR S excels in production environments due to its API-first design and F16 optimization, but alternatives may suit specific needs. For instance, Tesseract is free and customizable but requires significant tuning for accuracy, while Google Vision offers broad feature sets at a higher cost."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The table above provides a snapshot, but deeper analysis shows Nanonets OCR S has lower error rates on handwritten text (92% vs. 85% for Tesseract) and better support for non-Latin scripts. For teams already in cloud ecosystems, AWS Textract integrates seamlessly with other services, but Nanonets offers more predictable pricing and lower latency for pure OCR tasks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Refer to the "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tesseract",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Tesseract documentation"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for open-source details, and the "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://cloud.google.com/vision/docs",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Google Vision API reference"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for cloud-based comparisons. Choose based on your stack: Nanonets for balanced performance, Tesseract for budget constraints, or cloud providers for integrated workflows."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Known Limitations and Troubleshooting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Despite its strengths, Nanonets OCR S has constraints. It performs best on images between 150-600 DPI; lower resolutions may reduce accuracy, while higher ones increase latency without proportional gains. The model does not support real-time video OCR or animated GIFs, and complex mathematical notation extraction is limited. For non-Latin scripts, accuracy can drop below 90% for rare characters, so validate outputs for critical applications."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common issues include timeout errors for large files (over 10MB) or rate limiting during traffic spikes. Implement exponential backoff in your client, and use the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/status",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint for async jobs. If accuracy is low, preprocess images with tools like OpenCV to enhance contrast or deskew. Error code "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "422",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " indicates invalid parameters; check the "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://docs.nanonets.com/ocr-api/errors",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "API documentation"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for details."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Warning:",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Avoid sending sensitive data without encryption; use HTTPS and consider on-premises deployment for regulated industries. The API logs requests for quality assurance, so review data policies before integration."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deployment Notes for Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deploying Nanonets OCR S in production requires attention to scalability, monitoring, and security. Use containerization with Docker to ensure consistent environments, and orchestrate with Kubernetes for auto-scaling based on queue depth. Set up health checks using the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/health",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint, and integrate with observability tools like Prometheus to track latency and error rates."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For high availability, deploy across multiple regions and use load balancers to distribute traffic. Implement circuit breakers to handle API outages gracefully, and cache frequent requests with Redis to reduce load. Security-wise, rotate API keys regularly and restrict IP ranges via the dashboard. Test failover scenarios, such as switching to a backup OCR provider during downtime, to maintain service continuity."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In summary, Nanonets OCR S is a robust choice for teams needing reliable OCR at scale. Start by prototyping with the Python SDK, then move to asynchronous processing for production loads. For further reading, explore the "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://docs.nanonets.com/changelog",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Nanonets API changelog"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for updates, and join the community forum to share best practices. Next, benchmark it against your current solution using a sample dataset to quantify improvements in accuracy and cost."
          }
        ]
